@model Plantry.Web.Pages.Shared.ProductSearchCreateSheetViewModel
@using System.Text.Json

@*
    Shared product search / create sheet — a self-contained bottom-drawer fragment for picking or
    creating a catalog product.  Consumed by:
      - Recipes/Edit.cshtml  (ingredient add/edit — trackStock:true, qty+unit fields shown)
      - TakeStock walk pages (P4-7 inline add — trackStock depends on context, extra slot for count+location)

    ── Two-view architecture (plantry-nb4x) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    The sheet has two views, swapped in place via x-show — NOT a nested modal:

      SEARCH VIEW  (sheetView !== 'create')
        Product search input + htmx-driven listbox.
        A persistent "＋ @Model.CreateLabel" affordance sits below the search input and is always
        visible — it does not vanish when a product is selected (plantry-0zrc superseded).
        Clicking it sets sheetView = 'create' and draft.newStapleName = '' in-place.

      CREATE VIEW  (sheetView === 'create')
        Full-panel second view of the same flyout, same panel, content swapped in place.
        Header swaps to "@Model.CreateViewTitle" + "← Back to search" backlink.
        The host's ExtraFieldsPartial slot is rendered in both views so count+location fields
        are retained unchanged across the swap (required by plantry-l92u single-submit).
        Siblings extend the create-view body:
          plantry-40n6 — Group (optional) + "＋ Create group {name}" + variant preview line (this).
          plantry-y53t — wraps Unit + Category in a Defaults <details> collapsible.
          plantry-l92u — "Create & count" submit wiring (backend + island event).

    ── Alpine contract ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    The host page's x-data must expose:
      sheetOpen  : bool — controls x-show on this fragment
      sheetView  : 'search' | 'create' — which view is active (initialise to 'search' on sheet open)
      editingIdx : null | number — null = adding, number = editing existing row
      draft      : object — working copy of the row being added/edited:
                     { productId, productName, isUntracked, newStapleName, newStapleUnit,
                       qty, unitId, groupHeading,
                       newGroupId,   ← '' = standalone or no selection; non-empty = join existing group
                       newGroupName, ← '' = standalone; non-empty text = create new group or selection
                       ... }
      closeSheet()  — called by Cancel / Escape / overlay click
      saveSheet()   — called by the Add/Save (search view) or Create/Create & count (create view) button

    ── Group field (plantry-40n6) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    Rendered when Model.GroupOptions is not null (null = context does not support group-aware create).
    Three modes driven purely by (newGroupId, newGroupName):
      Standalone  : both empty — product created without a group (CreateProductCommand).
      New group   : newGroupId empty, newGroupName non-empty — creates group + this variant atomically
                    (CreateGroupedProductCommand).  Affordance: "+ Create group '{name}'" in listbox.
      Join group  : newGroupId non-empty — new product added as variant of the existing group
                    (CreateVariantCommand).  Affordance: pick an existing group from the listbox.

    The variant preview line below the Group field renders reactively:
      standalone  → hidden
      new group   → "Creates a new '{name}' group and adds '{product}' as its first variant."
      join group  → "Adds '{product}' as a variant of the existing '{name}' group."

    draft.newGroupId and draft.newGroupName are plain Alpine draft fields that the host's saveSheet()
    reads. The combobox listbox is pure Alpine (no htmx) — groupOptions are serialised server-side
    into the Alpine x-data and filtered client-side (group lists are small per household).

    ── Event contract ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    Inbound  — sheet-product-set (window): { detail: label string }
               Dispatched by the host when opening the sheet to pre-populate the search box.
               Handled by @sheet-product-set.window on the searchable-select wrapper.

    Outbound — pick-product (bubbles from inside the sheet to the .sheet element)
               Detail: { value: ProductId string, name: string, track: "true"|"false" }
               The host catches via @pick-product="selectProduct(draft, $event.detail)" on the sheet.

    ── TrackStock / slot ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    Model.TrackStock = true  → qty + unit fields are shown for tracked products (Recipes).
    Model.TrackStock = false → qty + unit fields are never shown (Take Stock — count lives elsewhere).
    Model.ExtraFieldsPartial → optional partial name rendered ONCE between the two views and the
                               action bar (e.g. Take Stock count + location fields, P4-7). Rendering
                               it once (always in DOM, always visible) avoids duplicate-id collisions
                               between the search and create views while preserving user-entered values
                               across the view swap.

    ── Context-aware params ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    Model.Noun              → noun used in search-view title / aria-label: "Add {Noun}" / "Edit {Noun}"
    Model.CreateViewTitle   → header title shown while in create view (default "New product")
    Model.ShowGroupHeading  → false hides the Recipes-only "Group (optional)" field (Take Stock)
    Model.CreateLabel       → label for the persistent create affordance button
    Model.StapleNamePlaceholder → placeholder for the name input in create view
    Model.GroupOptions      → null = hide group field; non-null = render group combobox

    ── Why x-show, not x-if ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    The sheet stays in the DOM (x-show, not x-if) so the nested searchable-select inits once at
    page load and the htmx product-search binding is established before the sheet first opens.
    Using x-if would re-mount the widget on every open, losing focus and triggering redundant htmx setup.
*@
@{
    // Serialise group options for Alpine. JsonSerializer.Serialize produces safe JSON; the result
    // is emitted into an x-data attribute that Razor HTML-encodes — Alpine reads the attribute
    // value after the browser decodes HTML entities, so &quot;/&amp; round-trip correctly.
    // Do NOT use Html.Raw here; the HTML-encoding is required for the attribute context.
    var groupOptionsJson = Model.GroupOptions is not null
        ? JsonSerializer.Serialize(Model.GroupOptions.Select(g => new { id = g.Id, name = g.Name }).ToList())
        : "null";
}

<div class="sheet" x-show="sheetOpen" x-cloak role="dialog" aria-modal="true"
     :aria-label="editingIdx === null ? 'Add @Model.Noun' : 'Edit @Model.Noun'"
     @@pick-product="selectProduct(draft, $event.detail)"
     @@keydown.escape="closeSheet()">
    <div class="sheet__overlay" @@click="closeSheet()"></div>
    <div class="sheet__panel">

        @* ── Header — title + close; when in create view adds "← Back to search" ── *@
        <header class="sheet__header">
            @* Search-view title *@
            <h2 class="sheet__title" x-show="sheetView !== 'create'"
                x-text="editingIdx === null ? 'Add @Model.Noun' : 'Edit @Model.Noun'"></h2>
            @* Create-view header: backlink + title (both rendered server-side to avoid layout flash) *@
            <div class="sheet__header-create" x-show="sheetView === 'create'">
                <button type="button" class="sheet__back"
                        @@click="sheetView = 'search'; draft.newStapleName = null; draft.productId = ''; draft.newStapleUnit = ''"
                        aria-label="Back to search">
                    &#8592; Back to search
                </button>
                <h2 class="sheet__title">@Model.CreateViewTitle</h2>
            </div>
            <button type="button" class="sheet__close" aria-label="Close" @@click="closeSheet()">&times;</button>
        </header>

        @* ════════════════ SEARCH VIEW ════════════════ *@
        <div x-show="sheetView !== 'create'">
            <div class="form-grid">
                @* ── Product — searchable-select ──────────────────────────────── *@
                <div class="form-grid__field form-grid__field--full">
                    <label class="form-grid__field__label">Product</label>
                    <div class="form-grid__field__control">
                        @*
                            htmx:afterSwap bubbles from the #prod-list-sheet <ul> to here (not the sibling
                            input), so 'open' is driven reactively from the result count — the popover shows
                            only when there are matches and never as an empty panel.
                        *@
                        <div class="searchable-select" x-data="searchableSelect()"
                             :data-initial-label="draft.productName"
                             @@sheet-product-set.window="query = $event.detail; open = false; highlighted = -1"
                             @@htmx:after-swap="open = ($event.target.children.length > 0)"
                             @@click.outside="open = false" @@keydown.escape.stop="open = false">
                            <input type="text" class="field__input" role="combobox" autocomplete="off"
                                   placeholder="Search products…"
                                   x-model="query"
                                   :aria-expanded="open"
                                   @@keydown.down.prevent="highlightNext()"
                                   @@keydown.up.prevent="highlightPrev()"
                                   @@keydown.enter.prevent="(function(){ const li = $refs.listbox && ($refs.listbox.querySelector('[aria-selected=true]') || $refs.listbox.querySelector('li')); if (li) li.click(); })()"
                                   name="q"
                                   id="prod-search-sheet"
                                   hx-get="@Model.SearchUrl"
                                   hx-trigger="keyup changed delay:250ms, focus"
                                   hx-target="#prod-list-sheet"
                                   hx-swap="innerHTML"
                                   hx-params="q" />
                            <ul class="searchable-select__listbox"
                                id="prod-list-sheet"
                                role="listbox"
                                x-ref="listbox"
                                x-show="open" x-cloak style="display:none">
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        @*
                            Persistent create affordance — always visible; does NOT vanish when a product
                            is selected (plantry-0zrc superseded). Clicking navigates the same flyout panel
                            to the create view in-place (sheetView = 'create') — no nested modal, no new scrim.
                            draft.newStapleName is initialised to '' (non-null) so the Recipes saveSheet
                            path and TakeStock bridge both detect "create mode" via the existing null-check.
                        *@
                        <div style="margin-top:var(--space-2)">
                            <button type="button"
                                    class="btn btn--ghost btn--sm"
                                    @@click="sheetView = 'create'; draft.newStapleName = draft.newStapleName ?? ''">
                                + @Model.CreateLabel
                            </button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                @if (Model.TrackStock)
                {
                    @*
                        Quantity — shown when:
                          - A product was picked from search (draft.productId is set), OR
                          - Editing a tracked inline-create row (draft.newIsTracked, plantry-orix),
                        but NOT for untracked/staple rows (draft.isUntracked).
                    *@
                    <div class="form-grid__field" x-show="!draft.isUntracked && (draft.productId || draft.newIsTracked)">
                        <label class="form-grid__field__label">Quantity</label>
                        <div class="form-grid__field__control">
                            <input type="number" class="field__input" step="any" min="0"
                                   placeholder="e.g. 50" x-model="draft.qty" />
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    @*
                        Unit — shown under the same conditions as Quantity above.
                        Also visible when editing a tracked inline-create row (draft.newIsTracked).
                    *@
                    <div class="form-grid__field" x-show="!draft.isUntracked && (draft.productId || draft.newIsTracked)">
                        <label class="form-grid__field__label">Unit</label>
                        <div class="form-grid__field__control">
                            <select class="field__input" x-model="draft.unitId">
                                <option value="">— Unit —</option>
                                @foreach (var u in Model.UnitOptions)
                                {
                                    <option value="@u.Value">@u.Text</option>
                                }
                            </select>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                }

                @*
                    Group heading — Recipes-only concept (ingredient sections). Hidden for Take Stock.
                    Gate: show for tracked rows (productId set) OR for staple/untracked rows
                    (newStapleName !== null). Previously always-visible; the newStapleName check
                    restores editability for staple rows that were previously always shown the field.
                *@
                @if (Model.ShowGroupHeading)
                {
                    <div class="form-grid__field form-grid__field--full"
                         x-show="draft.productId || draft.newStapleName !== null">
                        <label class="form-grid__field__label">Group (optional)</label>
                        <div class="form-grid__field__control">
                            <input type="text" class="field__input" placeholder="e.g. Sauce, Topping"
                                   x-model="draft.groupHeading" />
                        </div>
                    </div>
                }
            </div>

        </div>

        @* ════════════════ CREATE VIEW ════════════════ *@
        @*
            plantry-nb4x delivered the shell: Name + Unit fields + action bar.
            plantry-40n6 (this) adds: Group (optional) combobox + variant preview line.
            plantry-y53t will wrap Unit + Category in a Defaults <details> collapsible.
            plantry-l92u will wire the "Create & count" submit path.

            The group combobox Alpine component is scoped to its own x-data to avoid
            polluting the host's draft namespace. It writes back to draft.newGroupId
            and draft.newGroupName via $dispatch + the host's @create-group-set listener,
            or directly as a nested Alpine scope that has access to $parent.draft.
            We use direct parent-scope access (draft.newGroupId / draft.newGroupName)
            since the group combobox x-data is a child scope of the host's x-data.
        *@
        <div x-show="sheetView === 'create'">
            <div class="form-grid">
                <div class="form-grid__field form-grid__field--full">
                    <label class="form-grid__field__label" for="create-product-name">Name</label>
                    <div class="form-grid__field__control">
                        <input type="text" id="create-product-name" class="field__input"
                               placeholder="@Model.StapleNamePlaceholder"
                               x-model="draft.newStapleName"
                               autocomplete="off" />
                    </div>
                </div>

                @if (Model.GroupOptions is not null)
                {
                    @*
                        ── Group combobox (plantry-40n6) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
                        Unified combobox for the "Group" field in the create view. Three outcomes:
                          1. User leaves it empty → standalone product (draft.newGroupId = '', newGroupName = '').
                          2. User picks an existing group from the listbox → joins that group
                             (draft.newGroupId = existing group's ProductId, newGroupName = group's name).
                          3. User types a new name and picks "+ Create group '{name}'" → new group
                             (draft.newGroupId = '', newGroupName = typed name).

                        The listbox is scoped x-data with groupOptions injected from the server. The combobox
                        writes draft.newGroupId and draft.newGroupName directly (child scope has access to
                        $parent.draft via Alpine's scope chain). No htmx — group lists are small per household.

                        The variant preview line below the field renders reactively based on the draft state.
                    *@
                    <div class="form-grid__field form-grid__field--full"
                         x-data="{
                             groupOptions: @groupOptionsJson,
                             groupQuery: '',
                             groupOpen: false,
                             get filteredGroups() {
                                 const q = this.groupQuery.trim().toLowerCase();
                                 if (!q) return this.groupOptions;
                                 return this.groupOptions.filter(g => g.name.toLowerCase().includes(q));
                             },
                             pickGroup(g) {
                                 this.groupQuery    = g.name;
                                 draft.newGroupId   = g.id;
                                 draft.newGroupName = g.name;
                                 this.groupOpen     = false;
                             },
                             pickCreateGroup() {
                                 const name = this.groupQuery.trim();
                                 draft.newGroupId   = '';
                                 draft.newGroupName = name;
                                 this.groupOpen     = false;
                             },
                             clearGroup() {
                                 this.groupQuery    = '';
                                 draft.newGroupId   = '';
                                 draft.newGroupName = '';
                             }
                         }"
                         @@click.outside="groupOpen = false">
                        <label class="form-grid__field__label" for="create-product-group">
                            Group <span style="font-weight:400;text-transform:none;letter-spacing:0">(optional)</span>
                        </label>
                        <div class="form-grid__field__control" style="position:relative">
                            <input type="text" id="create-product-group" class="field__input"
                                   placeholder="Type to search or create a group…"
                                   x-model="groupQuery"
                                   autocomplete="off"
                                   @@focus="groupOpen = true"
                                   @@input="groupOpen = true; draft.newGroupId = ''; draft.newGroupName = ''"
                                   @@keydown.escape.stop="groupOpen = false; clearGroup()" />
                            @*
                                Listbox — shown when input is focused and either there are matches or the user
                                has typed a non-empty query (to show the "+ Create group" affordance).
                            *@
                            <ul class="searchable-select__listbox" role="listbox"
                                x-show="groupOpen && (filteredGroups.length > 0 || groupQuery.trim().length > 0)"
                                x-cloak style="display:none">
                                @* Existing groups matching the query *@
                                <template x-for="g in filteredGroups" :key="g.id">
                                    <li role="option" class="searchable-select__listbox-item"
                                        @@click="pickGroup(g)"
                                        x-text="g.name"></li>
                                </template>
                                @*
                                    "+ Create group '{name}'" affordance — shown only when the user has typed
                                    something that does not already exactly match an existing group name.
                                *@
                                <li role="option" class="searchable-select__listbox-item searchable-select__listbox-item--create"
                                    x-show="groupQuery.trim().length > 0 && !groupOptions.some(g => g.name.toLowerCase() === groupQuery.trim().toLowerCase())"
                                    @@click="pickCreateGroup()">
                                    <span>+ Create group</span>
                                    <span class="create-group-name" x-text="' “' + groupQuery.trim() + '”'"></span>
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        @*
                            ── Variant preview line ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
                            Per DM-19 depth-1 variant grouping. Shown only when Group is non-empty.
                            Three states:
                              new group   (newGroupId empty, newGroupName non-empty)
                                → "Creates a new '…' group and adds '…' as its first variant."
                              join group  (newGroupId non-empty)
                                → "Adds '…' as a variant of the existing '…' group."
                              no group    (both empty) → hidden.
                        *@
                        <div class="create-group-preview"
                             x-show="draft.newGroupName && draft.newGroupName.trim().length > 0"
                             x-cloak>
                            @* new-group path *@
                            <p x-show="!draft.newGroupId" class="create-group-preview__text create-group-preview__text--new">
                                <span>Creates a new </span>
                                <strong x-text="'“' + (draft.newGroupName || '') + '”'"></strong>
                                <span> group and adds </span>
                                <strong x-text="'“' + ((draft.newStapleName || '').trim() || 'this product') + '”'"></strong>
                                <span> as its first variant.</span>
                            </p>
                            @* join-existing-group path *@
                            <p x-show="draft.newGroupId" class="create-group-preview__text create-group-preview__text--join">
                                <span>Adds </span>
                                <strong x-text="'“' + ((draft.newStapleName || '').trim() || 'this product') + '”'"></strong>
                                <span> as a variant of the existing </span>
                                <strong x-text="'“' + (draft.newGroupName || '') + '”'"></strong>
                                <span> group.</span>
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                }

            </div>

            @*
                ── Defaults collapsible (plantry-y53t) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
                A <details> disclosure wrapping the two optional-to-see fields: Unit (required by
                CreateProductCommand) and Category (optional).  Collapsed by default so the create
                form stays compact; the user can expand when they want to change the defaults.

                Unit is bound to draft.newStapleUnit — the existing wire used by Recipes' hidden-input
                post (Input.Lines[n].NewStapleDefaultUnitId) and the TakeStock saveSheet() fallback.
                Category is bound to draft.newStapleCategoryId — a new optional draft field.
                Both are bound with x-model inside the Alpine x-data of the host, so no inner x-data
                scope is needed here.
            *@
            <details class="sheet-defaults">
                <summary class="sheet-defaults__summary">Defaults</summary>
                <div class="sheet-defaults__body">
                    <div class="form-grid__field form-grid__field--full">
                        <label class="form-grid__field__label" for="create-product-unit">Unit</label>
                        <div class="form-grid__field__control">
                            <select id="create-product-unit" class="field__input" x-model="draft.newStapleUnit">
                                <option value="">— Unit —</option>
                                @foreach (var u in Model.UnitOptions)
                                {
                                    <option value="@u.Value">@u.Text</option>
                                }
                            </select>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-grid__field form-grid__field--full">
                        <label class="form-grid__field__label" for="create-product-category">Category</label>
                        <div class="form-grid__field__control">
                            <select id="create-product-category" class="field__input" x-model="draft.newStapleCategoryId">
                                <option value="">— None —</option>
                                @foreach (var c in Model.CategoryOptions)
                                {
                                    <option value="@c.Value">@c.Text</option>
                                }
                            </select>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </details>
        </div>

        @*
            ── Host extra-fields slot — rendered ONCE, always in DOM ─────────────────────────────
            Placed between the two view sections and the action bars so the user's count and location
            values are retained as-is when switching between the search and create views (no re-mount,
            no duplicate IDs). Rendering once also avoids Playwright strict-mode violations from
            elements such as #add-count appearing twice in the DOM.
        *@
        @if (Model.ExtraFieldsPartial is { } slot)
        {
            <partial name="@slot" />
        }

        @*
            ── Action bars — two bars, one visible at a time via x-show ──────────────────────────
            Two separate action bars are needed because the primary button label differs:
              search view  → "Add" / "Save"
              create view  → "Create & count" (Take Stock, ShowCreateAndCount=true)
                          OR "Create" (Recipes and other surfaces, ShowCreateAndCount=false)
            Both bars remain in the DOM (x-show, not x-if) so Alpine bindings stay alive.
            Tests use .First / .Last to explicitly select the desired button; strict mode only
            fires for un-indexed locator calls that match multiple DOM nodes.

            NOTE on encoding: The bare "&" in "Create & count" is inside an @if block (static text),
            so Razor does NOT HTML-encode it automatically — `&` must be written as `&amp;` here.
            This is intentional and NOT a double-encode: the outer @if expression uses Html.Raw
            semantics for Razor literal text (it is not inside an @() expression).
            To confirm: snapshots show `Create &amp; count` in the rendered HTML — correct for &.
        *@
        <div class="sheet__actions" x-show="sheetView !== 'create'">
            <button type="button" class="btn btn--primary" @@click="saveSheet()"
                    x-text="editingIdx === null ? 'Add' : 'Save'"></button>
            <button type="button" class="btn btn--ghost" @@click="closeSheet()">Cancel</button>
        </div>
        <div class="sheet__actions" x-show="sheetView === 'create'">
            <button type="button" class="btn btn--primary" @@click="saveSheet()">
                @if (Model.ShowCreateAndCount) { <text>Create &amp; count</text> } else { <text>Create</text> }
            </button>
            <button type="button" class="btn btn--ghost"
                    @@click="sheetView = 'search'; draft.newStapleName = null; draft.productId = ''; draft.newStapleUnit = ''">
                Cancel
            </button>
        </div>

    </div>
</div>
